More from FactSet »










Description




SunEdison, Inc. is a renewable energy development company. The Company develops, finances, installs, owns and operates renewable power plants, and delivers electricity to its residential, commercial, government and utility customers. The Company provides customers with asset management, operations and maintenance, monitoring and reporting services. The Company's asset management services include billing and reporting, finance and accounting, tax and audit services, vendor management and warranty claims management. The Company also maintains a database of system performance and product information for its own products, as well as third-party components. The Company offers SunEdison Connect, a Web-based software application that gives access to data and services via an online monitoring portal. Its operations and maintenance (O&M) services cover all electrical and mechanical components, including arrays, inverters, trackers, combiners, racking and wiring.


