Managers




128
IT employees




$85.3MEST.
IT Budget




SunEdison (formerly MEMC Electronic Materials, Inc.) designs, manufactures, and sells renewable energy products. The company operates manufacturing facilities throughout the world, including Europe, Japan, Malaysia, Taiwan, South Korea, and the United States.  The company changed its name to SunEdison and… MoreSunEdison (formerly MEMC Electronic Materials, Inc.) designs, manufactures, and sells renewable energy products. The company operates manufacturing facilities throughout the world, including Europe, Japan, Malaysia, Taiwan, South Korea, and the United States.  The company changed its name to SunEdison and spun off its Semiconductor division in 2013.
SunEdison (formerly MEMC Electronic Materials, Inc.) designs, manufactures, and sells silicon wafers for the semiconductor industry worldwide. The company operates manufacturing facilities throughout the world, including Europe, Japan, Malaysia, Taiwan, South Korea, and the United States.  The company changed its… MoreSunEdison (formerly MEMC Electronic Materials, Inc.) designs, manufactures, and sells silicon wafers for the semiconductor industry worldwide. The company operates manufacturing facilities throughout the world, including Europe, Japan, Malaysia, Taiwan, South Korea, and the United States.  The company changed its name to SunEdison in 2013.

SunEdison Inc. (formerly MEMC Electronic Materials Inc.) maintains the majority of its internal Information Technology department at the corporate headquarters in St. Peters, Missouri supplemented by a small team at the Sherman, TX location.

The IT Facilities team is responsible for all IT initiatives relating to application implementation, software development, customer service enhancement, and procurement. This team is broken into IT Operations, IT Services, Global Network Services, and Database Management. SunEdison utilizes many SAP applications to support these initiatives. Currently, the company utilizes Leap Consulting LLC to support its order to cash SAP ERP environment. Software architecture and security systems teams support sales operations, product inventory and customer service.

The data storage systems team focuses on improving international business operations with a strong emphasis on EMC technologies.

SunEdison's organization-wide data volume is approximately 100 TB – 1 PB and is growing at an annual rate of 6-10%.  Its data environment consists of somewhat integrated (25-50% of data on single database architecture) data that is primarily deployed on premises in a purpose-built appliance.  The company uses relational databases to store data primarily sourced from enterprise applications.  

SunEdison's IT budget is typically finalized in Q3. 

IT Intelligence Snippets:
• Less than 30% of IT staff is dedicated to the sustenance of its ERP platform. 
• Expects approximately 12 releases/updates a year with its current ERP solution.
• SunEdison had previously decreased spending in data storage, data center infrastructure, network security, capacity planning, and disaster recovery. Storage, SAN and backup are the top infrastructure priorities. The company is looking to deploy backup solutions. The Storage group has previously looked to IT vendors to address pain points that decrease backup traffic, increase storage, and decrease backup licensing costs.





